    grouped_data = defaultdict(list)

    # Group the data by the first column value (key)
    for entry in test_list:
        key = entry[0]
        grouped_data[key].append(entry)

    final_transformed_data = []

    for key, group in grouped_data.items():

        second_row = [key] + [entry[3] for entry in group]
        final_transformed_data.append(first_row)
        final_transformed_data.append(second_row)

    return final_transformed_data

        grouped_data[key].append(entry)

    final_transformed_data = []

    for key, group in grouped_data.items():
        first_row = [''] + [entry[1] + entry[2] for entry in group]
        second_row = [key] + [entry[3] for entry in group]
        final_transformed_data.append(first_row)
        final_transformed_data.append(second_row)

    return final_transformed_data
